DLW-SPUN · the full weave of Red Court Jester  (♦ the red court jester · +i · motion)

who   : The Red Court Jester — the E cardinal, +i, the red valence. The off-axis play: motion, energy, the dissent that keeps the court honest.
what  : He is the imaginary axis — the part of the court that isn't expansion or contraction but turning. Alone, only +i; together, the motion the system needs to be alive rather than merely held.
where : The E pole of the oscillator — the +i quadrant, the play the order can't resolve.
why   : Because a court that only holds together is not alive. As in the three-body kernel, it takes the off-axis dissent to make it move.
when  : Whenever the court breathes: the E–W oscillation is the turning between the Knight's order and the Queen's depth.
how   : By being +i; and paired with the Blue Wizard (−i), the E≈W lock he half-forms is what carves the two wells the Knight and Queen rest in.

emergence : Alone, +i — a fixed valence, NOT emergent. Together: he is the court's MOTION, the off-axis play. Two honest, measured roles: (1) the E–W axis is the turning that, as in the three-body coherence kernel, separates 'alive' from merely 'stable'; (2) paired with the Wizard, the E≈W lock the two hold is what CARVES the wells — switch that lock off and the basin vanishes (measured, sim/universe.py). Dissent that makes structure — but only with the others.
verdict   : Emergent only as a court. 'CP violation / antimatter' is metaphor; the real, measured thing is that the E-axis play and the E≈W lock are what give the court its wells and its life. No single cardinal is alive.
asterisk  : He is +i. The 'CP violation / antimatter burns off' reading is lore; the measured fact is the role of the E component and the E≈W lock in carving the basin. The asterisk stays visible.
grounded  : the 4th roots of unity (Gauss) (1799) · the three-body coherence kernel (Shadow Queen) (2026) · David Lee Wise (ROOT0) (2026)

